  "texts": [
    "There are constraints from these collisions in the global analyses of the nPDFs used in the calculations.",
    "For example, EPS09 [176] used π 0 data from RHIC to constrain the gluon distribution and EPPS16 [138] used LHC p-Pb data on W ± and Z 0 production to separate the antiquark distributions in the sea at high Q 2 and on dijet data to further constrain the gluon distribution.",
    "The centrality dependence of R dAu ( p T) was used to study the centrality dependence of shadowing [232].",
    "Fixed-target pA data were used to constrain the J/ψ absorption cross section [235].",
    "However, absorption is considered negligible at the LHC collider energies and is not included in the calculation [233]."
